President Muhammadu Buhari has berated his Service Chiefs over the spate of insecurity across the country. Buhari said the Security Chiefs have not done their best in curbing the issue of insecurity in the country. The President also warned that “excuses will no longer be tolerated,” because he expects them to live up to expectations. The President had earlier met with all Security Chiefs at the Presidential Villa, Abuja. Buhari’s displeasure was disclosed by the National Security Adviser (NSA), Maj. Gen. Babagana Monguno (Rtd.). Addressing State House Correspondents in Abuja after the meeting, Monguno said the President was unhappy with the current state of security in Nigeria. Monguno quoted Buhari as saying the best of the security chiefs was not good enough for the challenges facing the nation. He disclosed that the president also expressed displeasure over the lack of synergy amongst security forces.